Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2Mn0.5Co0.5O3 (LSMCO) films for the use as contact layers or protective coatings in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) have been deposited on glass substrates by pulsed laser deposition (PLD).
Titulo: Electrical and structural properties of La0.8Sr0.2Mn0.5Co0.5O3±δ films produced by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: PLD is an obvious technique for thin film production of complex oxides, because of the ability to transfer material stoichiometrically from a multicomponent target to a growing film.
Titulo: Electrical and structural properties of La0.8Sr0.2Mn0.5Co0.5O3±δ films produced by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: In the present study, films were deposited at substrate temperatures of 473 and 573 K and in different oxygen background pressures.
Titulo: Electrical and structural properties of La0.8Sr0.2Mn0.5Co0.5O3±δ films produced by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: The influence of the process parameters, in particular of the oxygen background gas pressure, on the electrical conductivity and structure of the films is investigated.
Titulo: Electrical and structural properties of La0.8Sr0.2Mn0.5Co0.5O3±δ films produced by pulsed laser deposition
